defaultWhile our bi
defaultlingual schools and shared communities demonstrate that it is possible for Jews and Arabs to peacefully coexist, interact, and become friends, the experience of cooperation that we have demonstrated will have a limited impact if it remains known only to th
defaultose who have personally experienced it. Therefore, HIH has hired an 
defaultOrganizational Journalist
default to join the team, and help publicize our story of an inclusive society to as wide an audience as possible
default in Hebrew, English and Arabic
default.  HIH’s “doing” in the bil
defaultingual schools and in the shared communities will inform the telling
default, which will illustrate the viability of inclusion, shared society and equality.  
defaultThis will counter 
defaultthe 
default feelings
default of helplessness and despair that exists in no small part because of the media’s highlighting negative stories. Our stories 
defaultthat appear in radio segments, television reports, in the Israeli and international press, 
